> straightened out all the normal problems,bad gas clogged injection, etc. 
> I have gotten the bus to run and have been able to drive it. The problem 
> is sometimes the ignition switch will not trigger the starter. This seems 
> to happen almost at random. The switch will only turn over the starter 
> about 1 in 20 times. I have replaced my battery terminals and wires, 
> cleaned every contact on the starter, checked for voltage at the starter, 
> and everything seems ok. is their something I don't know about the 
> solenoid that I should take into account? Any possible information or 
> things to try would be greatly appreciated. Thanks

Had a '72 Super Beetle (Italian Spec as I was living in Italy) that 
developed this problem and I had to replace the ignition switch. The little 
nylon nubs that the key housing pushed against finally got worn down to 
nothing.


